 *
 * A "scomp" is a pair of files on disk:
 *   Name.sc.html   — declarative template, may arrive char-by-char
 *   Name.sc.js     — logic class (TS allowed), must arrive whole
 *
 * The runtime compiles the .sc.html into a pure (vals, ctx) => ReactNode
 * function and wraps it + the logic class in a single real React class
 * component (StreamableComponent). Missing pieces degrade gracefully:
 * no html → sized placeholder, no js → template renders against {}.
 *
 * Public surface (on window):
 *   __updateComponentHtml(name, html)        — recompile + re-render, keeps DOM/state
 *   __updateComponentJs(name, src)           — transpile, HMR-swap logic instances
 *   __setComponentJsStreaming(name, on)      — toggle "JS incoming" pulse
